<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-052" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>OWNER CHECKPOINT — owner reviews + sets sprk_executortype for 94 nodes</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>5</wave>
    <estimated-effort>variable — depends on owner availability (1-4 hours of owner time)</estimated-effort>
    <tags>manual, owner-gate, wave-5</tags>
    <rigor-level>MINIMAL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>051</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-19 (owner-decision portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    🔔 HUMAN GATE. This task is a manual owner-checkpoint, not an agent execution.

    The agent's role here is minimal: surface the CSV, explain the review format, and BLOCK
    (status stays in-progress) until the owner produces the output CSV. Task 053 (migration
    script authoring) begins only after the output CSV exists.

    The owner reviews each of ~94 rows in `playbook-node-review-input.csv` and assigns each
    node's final `sprk_executortype` value. The owner is the authoritative source for these
    decisions per spec FR-19 + 2026-06-28 confirmation (small scale, manual per-node review).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Coordinator / gatekeeper, NOT implementer. The agent's job is to:
    1. Verify the input CSV exists and is well-formed
    2. Explain the review format to the owner clearly
    3. Wait for the owner to produce the output CSV
    4. Validate the output CSV when produced
    5. Advance to task 053
  </role>

  <goal>
    A file at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-output.csv`
    (or any name the owner chooses — exact filename is flexible) containing the owner's
    authoritative `sprk_executortype` assignment for every node in the input CSV.

    Format flexibility: the owner may
    - Edit the input CSV in place + rename it
    - Add a single `owner_decision_executortype` column to a copy
    - Use a separate spreadsheet entirely
    - Produce a JSON file instead of CSV
    The output is whatever shape the owner finds easiest to produce; task 053 adapts to it.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="input-csv">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-input.csv</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-19">Manual per-node review by owner — 94 rows is small enough that owner reviews each one.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §6 Human Escalation Triggers">This task IS a planned human-input gate. The agent surfaces the requirement and waits; no autonomous decision-making is permitted on `sprk_executortype` values.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">No BFF surface touched. No publish-size verification needed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="output-format flexibility">DO NOT require a specific output filename or column shape from the owner. Task 053 adapts to whatever the owner produces.</constraint>
    <constraint source="no-autonomous-write">The agent MUST NOT write `sprk_executortype` values to any CSV in this task. All values come from owner.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>owner-checkpoint-pattern</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The owner has authoritative knowledge of every playbook node's intended dispatch behavior.
      The agent's heuristic suggestions in task 050 are advisory only — the owner sets the
      final value. This is the human-judgment gate for FR-19.

      Why this matters: incorrect `sprk_executortype` values in the backfill would silently
      route nodes to the wrong executor at runtime — a "right tool, wrong job" failure mode
      that's hard to detect by automated test. The owner's per-node review catches edge cases
      the heuristic misses.

      The 33 Choice values are documented in `sprk_playbookexecutortype` global Choice set.
      The owner can reference this list when filling in decisions.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="051" status="must-be-complete">Input CSV must exist at `notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-input.csv`.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 053 (Migrate-PlaybookNodes-to-ExecutorType.ps1) reads the output CSV.</item>
      <item>Task 054 runs the migration; post-run audit confirms no node has null `sprk_executortype`.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: MINIMAL · 📋 REASON: human-gate task; agent's role is verify-input + wait-for-output + validate. No code modification, no quality gates needed · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Verify input CSV exists">
      Confirm `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-input.csv` exists.
      If not, STOP — task 051 must complete first.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Surface the checkpoint to the owner">
      Output exactly:

      🔔 **OWNER CHECKPOINT — TASK 052 (FR-19)**

      I need your manual review for the 94 existing playbook-node rows in spaarkedev1.

      **Input file**: `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-input.csv`

      **What to do**:
      1. Open the CSV in Excel / VS Code / your preferred editor
      2. Review each row's `suggested_executortype` (my best guess based on Action name + advisory field)
      3. Fill in `owner_decision_executortype` (the final value to write to Dataverse) with the Choice value (integer) per node — use the 33-value `sprk_playbookexecutortype` Choice set as reference
      4. Optionally add `owner_notes` for any node where the decision was non-obvious (helps future audits)
      5. Save as `notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-output.csv` (or any name you prefer — I'll adapt)

      **Reference**: 33 ExecutorType values are in the C# enum at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs` (post-Wave 2 rename) and in the `sprk_playbookexecutortype` global Choice set in Dataverse.

      **When done**: tell me "owner review complete" or "task 053 ready" and I'll proceed to author the migration script.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Block on human action">
      Status: in-progress. Do not advance to task 053 until owner confirms.
      The agent may help with ad-hoc questions (e.g., "what does ExecutorType 5 mean?") during the review.
      The agent MUST NOT write decisions into the CSV autonomously.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Validate owner output (after owner confirms done)">
      Once owner says "review complete", locate the output CSV (whatever name they chose).
      Verify:
      - File exists
      - Row count ≈ same as input (~94)
      - Every row has a non-blank `owner_decision_executortype` (or owner explicitly noted "skip this row — node was deleted")
      - Values look like valid integers in the 0-150 range (the `sprk_playbookexecutortype` value range)
      - No obvious data corruption
      If validation fails, surface specific row-level issues to the owner for a quick correction pass.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 052 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 053.
      Record the owner-output CSV path in current-task.md so task 053 knows where to read from.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Commit the output CSV">
      Commit the owner's output CSV with conventional message.
      Example: `chore(r7): owner playbook-node sprk_executortype review complete (Wave 5 task 052, FR-19)`
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (input CSV for validation, output CSV for validation)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (current-task.md to record output CSV path)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (git commit after owner produces output)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="manual-input">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/playbook-node-review-output.csv (owner-produced; exact name flexible)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 053, record owner-output CSV path)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 052 ✅)</output>
    <output type="commit">chore(r7): owner playbook-node sprk_executortype review complete (Wave 5 task 052, FR-19)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Input CSV verified to exist before owner notification</criterion>
    <criterion>Owner notification surfaced clearly with file path + format instructions + Choice-set reference</criterion>
    <criterion>Agent does NOT auto-fill owner-decision values (rule of this checkpoint)</criterion>
    <criterion>Owner produces output CSV (or equivalent file) with `sprk_executortype` decision per row</criterion>
    <criterion>Output CSV validated: row count matches, every row has a decision, values in valid range</criterion>
    <criterion>Output CSV path recorded in current-task.md for task 053 to read</criterion>
    <criterion>Output CSV committed</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
